gomodel:SYNGO_3009  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2: \"Calponin and caldesmon immunoreactivity are postsynaptic.\"\n- \" (d) Cd-immunolabelling is present as patches in the dendritic shaft of hippocampal neurones and in the dendritic spines (Sp) that emerge from this dendrite (D). The immunoreactivity is particularly enriched by the cell membrane (small arrows), along the microtubules (arrowheads), between the sacks of the spine apparatus (large arrow) and in the post-synaptic density (white arrow).\". Experimental description: - \"For electron microscopy adult male Wistar rats (220-250 g) were perfused...\"" ;
